{"ts":"2026-07-06T08:03:05.997Z","author":"maintainer-agent","op":"create","patch":[{"op":"replace","path":"/body","value":"GitHub: https://github.com/unbraind/pm-cli/issues/443\n\n## Problem\nThe structured error envelope carries two constant-prose fields on every error (`required`: \"Use values that match documented command constraints.\"; `why`: \"Validation protects data consistency...\"). They never vary by error and carry no actionable signal — pure token overhead in retry loops.\n\n## Proposed fix\nLean error mode (or simply omit constant `why`/`required` under --json unless error-specific): keep `code`, `detail`, `examples`, `next_steps`, `recovery.suggested_retry`. Verbose prose stays for human/TTY.\n\n## Definition of done\nJSON errors drop generic boilerplate (or --lean-errors/PM_LEAN_ERRORS added); error-envelope spec updated; agent docs note the mode. Related: pm-gdi7 covers unknown-option did-you-mean in the same envelope."},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/id","value":"pm-g9xk"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/title","value":"GH-443: lean error mode — drop constant required/why boilerplate from structured errors"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/description","value":"Dogfood GH-443: every structured error carries two constant prose fields (required/why) that never vary by error; keep only actionable fields in lean mode. Duplicate check: pm-gdi7 covers unknown-option suggestions, not envelope size; no other overlap."},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/type","value":"Feature"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/status","value":"open"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/priority","value":2},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/tags","value":["agent-ux","area:cli","gh-issue","token-efficiency"]},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/created_at","value":"2026-07-06T08:03:05.997Z"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/updated_at","value":"2026-07-06T08:03:05.997Z"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/author","value":"maintainer-agent"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/estimated_minutes","value":90},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/acceptance_criteria","value":"JSON errors omit generic constant prose while keeping code/detail/examples/next_steps/recovery; error-envelope spec updated; mode documented for agents"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/parent","value":"pm-mpbb"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/risk","value":"low"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/confidence","value":"high"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/dependencies","value":[{"id":"pm-gdi7","kind":"related","created_at":"2026-07-06T08:03:05.997Z"}]}],"before_hash":"3cc22dff72be7b14824654a7a64ea62b04799939b2fee54c1b5f52ca60bf6df0","after_hash":"bf343c5838f812a94cb2452d3202c8e3c146f2c2c744918c7d6f265a29e9858a","message":""}
