{"ts":"2026-07-15T19:27:27.234Z","author":"maintainer-agent","op":"note_add","patch":[{"op":"replace","path":"/metadata/updated_at","value":"2026-07-15T19:27:27.234Z"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/notes","value":[{"created_at":"2026-07-15T19:27:27.232Z","author":"maintainer-agent","text":"Fresh evidence 2026-07-15 (review pass #89): a one-token command typo (pm lst) returns ~20 lines / ~150 tokens of constant scaffolding (What happened / What is required / Why / Examples / Next steps / Recovery bundle) around the only two load-bearing lines: the error name and \"Did you mean: list?\". Worse, for unknown-OPTION errors the Error: headline and the \"What happened:\" paragraph are the IDENTICAL sentence twice (observed on --statuss). Lean mode should collapse to headline + suggestion + one recovery hint; the full bundle stays behind --verbose or a config key. Duplicate-sentence dedup is worth doing even before lean mode ships."}]}],"before_hash":"797ee4aae47b9ebed0464b6d7c0446565770bfa64ebee1fb1bc80463e65466c6","after_hash":"e07daff12b20b30e052bae581a9dea14d3d6ebcb2607effd6e92d878f1b953c0"}
